Bungoma MCAs have collected signatures in a bid to pass a motion to remover speaker Emmanuel Situma. Thirty MCAs accuse him of incompetence, lacking independence, pushing for fictious payments and flouting of procurement procedures. Speaking to the Star on Friday, Lwandanyi MCA Tonny Barasa, who is among those who signed the petition, said the speaker had failed to guide the assembly. Reached for comment, Situma said he will react to the allegations on the floor of the house However, Bungoma Governor Wyclife Wangamati has opposed the move by ward reps to impeach the speaker, saying it was to early.